# Relational Databases

Relational databases are a powerful way to organize and manage data using tables, rows, and columns. As you read the following articles, consider:

- How did early database systems influence the development of relational databases?
- What criteria can be used to evaluate the design and effectiveness of a relational database?

## Recommended Reading

1. [Relational Data Model 101: Key Components & Benefits by Anina Ot](https://www.datamation.com/big-data/relational-data-model/) (8 min)
2. [Introduction to Relational Databases from MariaDB](https://mariadb.com/kb/en/introduction-to-relational-databases/) (4 min)
3. [The Relational Data Model by Nguyen Kim Anh and Adrienne Watt](https://opentextbc.ca/dbdesign01/chapter/chapter-7-the-relational-data-model/) (16 min)
